This is the sports paper from last week.

118
00:07:25,415 --> 00:07:27,495
I've had my eye on this guy for a while.

119
00:07:28,241 --> 00:07:30,614
Wow! He pitched three perfect games in a row.

120
00:07:30,701 --> 00:07:35,590
"With sharp knuckleballs, no doubt this super
high school level pitcher will join the pro league."

121
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:38,137
The next day, I went and watched them practice.

122
00:07:39,082 --> 00:07:40,693
Everyone should look at this.

123
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:43,724
Here we go.

124
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:50,684
Strike!

125
00:07:51,587 --> 00:07:53,031
That's one heck of a curveball.

126
00:07:53,182 --> 00:07:55,296
He's like major league caliber.

127
00:07:55,547 --> 00:07:56,825
It gets even better.

128
00:07:57,079 --> 00:08:00,243
Watch some footage where we get a
closeup of the pitcher's throwing hand.

129
00:08:01,902 --> 00:08:03,402
There. Take a look.

130
00:08:03,466 --> 00:08:04,806
See something strange?

131
00:08:04,831 --> 00:08:05,482
