255
00:14:25,789 --> 00:14:27,129
Strike! Batter out.

256
00:14:31,198 --> 00:14:31,655
Out!

257
00:14:55,675 --> 00:14:56,810
Ball four!

258
00:14:57,035 --> 00:14:58,270
Not looking good.

259
00:15:00,948 --> 00:15:01,523
Out!

260
00:15:03,443 --> 00:15:04,103
Safe!

261
00:15:04,316 --> 00:15:06,222
This is a total crisis.

262
00:15:06,768 --> 00:15:08,642
We should use abilities as well.

263
00:15:09,357 --> 00:15:10,727
Specifically...?

264
00:15:10,893 --> 00:15:13,282
You need to take over the opponents' batters.

265
00:15:13,589 --> 00:15:17,845
What I want you to do is make the last two of
them listless so they barely swing their bats.

266
00:15:17,996 --> 00:15:19,710
Throw outside of the strike zone.

267
00:15:19,850 --> 00:15:22,202
Just be careful to not throw a wild pitch.

268
00:15:22,227 --> 00:15:23,408
Yeah, got it.

269
00:15:23,472 --> 00:15:25,377
All right now, I'm counting on you.

270
00:15:26,499 --> 00:15:27,388
Play ball!

271
00:15:29,123 --> 00:15:32,277
Never thought I'd use my powers for something like this.

272
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:37,292
Strike!

273
00:15:37,531 --> 00:15:38,864
Huh? What the...?

274
00:15:39,098 --> 00:15:39,947
What's the matter?

275
00:15:44,185 --> 00:15:45,179
Strike two!

276
00:15:45,332 --> 00:15:46,362
Hey, are you all right?

277
00:15:47,135 --> 00:15:48,608
Yeah, totally fine.

278
00:15:49,124 --> 00:15:50,949
It's two outs with the next guy.

279
00:15:52,936 --> 00:15:57,937
Arifumi, if you want to be that thorough
in winning this thing, we have to go all out!

280
00:15:59,477 --> 00:16:00,580
Catcher!

281
00:16:05,907 --> 00:16:06,763
Safe!

282
00:16:08,761 --> 00:16:09,622
Takato.

283
00:16:10,857 --> 00:16:12,328
Wait, what the hell happened?

284
00:16:12,511 --> 00:16:14,407
I didn't think that far ahead.

285
00:16:14,455 --> 00:16:15,995
Did he steal home base?

286
00:16:16,020 --> 00:16:17,693
Damn, damn, damn!

287
00:16:18,151 --> 00:16:20,126
Guess we ain't winnin' this one.

288
00:16:21,768 --> 00:16:23,556
Strike! Batter out!

289
00:16:23,737 --> 00:16:26,159
Just make sure that you hit the ball when you bunt.

290
00:16:26,238 --> 00:16:29,936
Then use your ability to run past
first base, and don't forget to touch it.

291
00:16:30,153 --> 00:16:32,317
Are you sure that they'll see me make it there?

292
00:16:32,479 --> 00:16:35,198
I'll record the evidence with a super‐high‐speed camera.

293
00:16:35,382 --> 00:16:36,277
Understood.

294
00:16:43,214 --> 00:16:44,325
Strike!

295
00:16:45,644 --> 00:16:46,746
Strike two!

296
00:16:47,493 --> 00:16:49,785
If I screw up the next one, I'm out.

297
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:52,958
Here it comes, four‐eyes.

298
00:16:59,646 --> 00:17:00,252
Yes!

299
00:17:05,283 --> 00:17:07,188
He touched first base, it's plain as day.

300
00:17:07,891 --> 00:17:09,900
Come on now, it's safe. Call safe!

301
00:17:11,622 --> 00:17:12,852
Safe!

302
00:17:13,809 --> 00:17:15,047
What the heck happened?

303
00:17:15,619 --> 00:17:18,261
That was great. We won't let it go to waste.

304
00:17:18,464 --> 00:17:19,991
I need a pinch runner!

305
00:17:21,738 --> 00:17:25,402
Yusa's weak, but I'll use my
own game sense to hit the ball.

306
00:17:32,101 --> 00:17:33,100
All right!

307
00:17:33,457 --> 00:17:35,194
That's the way. It was awesome!

308
00:17:35,219 --> 00:17:37,671
It's your turn to bat now, so what are you going to do?

309
00:17:37,878 --> 00:17:42,137
A sacrifice bunt, and once it succeeds,
one base hit will get us a walk‐off.

310
00:17:42,184 --> 00:17:45,106
Huh? I can't hit like that with my ability.

311
00:17:45,210 --> 00:17:48,067
How about you go face things head on once in a while?

312
00:17:49,408 --> 00:17:51,977
Show me the fiend that cheats on tests.

313
00:18:02,379 --> 00:18:05,371
Please hit it!

314
00:18:10,706 --> 00:18:11,484
First base!

315
00:18:11,509 --> 00:18:13,039
They're just a bunch of amateurs!

316
00:18:13,619 --> 00:18:14,206
Out!

317
00:18:17,525 --> 00:18:19,849
I have to face this crap head on?

318
00:18:20,564 --> 00:18:22,301
Lead! Lead!

319
00:18:24,787 --> 00:18:26,098
Strike!

320
00:18:27,239 --> 00:18:28,056
Strike two!

321
00:18:28,081 --> 00:18:28,763
Damn!

322
00:18:36,452 --> 00:18:37,467
Foul ball!

323
00:18:38,371 --> 00:18:39,816
I finally hit it.

324
00:18:42,402 --> 00:18:43,371
Foul!

325
00:18:44,234 --> 00:18:45,171
Foul!

326
00:18:46,115 --> 00:18:47,052
Foul!

327
00:18:48,806 --> 00:18:50,611
His timing is inching closer.

328
00:18:50,726 --> 00:18:52,595
I'll move it a bit more on this one.

329
00:19:02,804 --> 00:19:04,709
Crap! It's all over.

330
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:08,407
It's not over. Move it. He fumbled!

331
00:19:11,193 --> 00:19:11,800
Safe!

332
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:15,004
We can do this. I have the game sense!

333
00:19:15,029 --> 00:19:16,109
Takato, home!

334
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:31,133
Safe! That's the game!

335
00:19:33,329 --> 00:19:35,371
Did you see that? I ruled!

336
00:19:38,661 --> 00:19:40,310
That was amazing, Yusarin!

337
00:19:40,335 --> 00:19:41,176
So did we win?

338
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:43,454
Yes, by the skin of our teeth.

339
00:19:44,899 --> 00:19:46,692
We won. That's awesome.

340
00:19:47,629 --> 00:19:48,438
All right!

341
00:19:49,636 --> 00:19:53,467
Wait, why am I getting so happy about something like this?

342
00:19:56,177 --> 00:19:57,709
We were victorious.

343
00:19:58,050 --> 00:20:01,249
Please never use that ability again, ever.

344
00:20:03,376 --> 00:20:05,409
I'm just an ordinary pitcher.

345
00:20:05,854 --> 00:20:08,513
But Takato, the catcher, is different.

346
00:20:09,076 --> 00:20:12,282
He's a catcher that really
deserves to be in the spotlight.

347
00:20:12,473 --> 00:20:14,997
The two of us have played together for a long time.

348
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:18,234
He knew that the baseball team at our school was weak.

349
00:20:18,758 --> 00:20:21,742
But still he chose to pair up with me.

350
00:20:22,437 --> 00:20:27,009
I just wanted to take him to nationals,
even if it meant using this power.

351
00:20:27,174 --> 00:20:31,101
The nationals, that big stage
where even pros would notice him.

352
00:20:31,126 --> 00:20:35,505
So instead of personal gain, you were
using your ability for your friendship.

353
00:20:35,767 --> 00:20:36,640
That's right.

354
00:20:36,814 --> 00:20:40,055
We won the game today because
we cheated with our abilities.

355
00:20:40,122 --> 00:20:42,933
But you've been cheating while pitching for quite a while.

356
00:20:44,024 --> 00:20:46,397
But there are people who will notice him out there,

357
00:20:46,587 --> 00:20:48,230
even if you don't cheat,

358
00:20:48,675 --> 00:20:52,190
and it doesn't matter if it's in
college or in the business leagues.

359
00:20:52,389 --> 00:20:54,689
You can keep watch over him as his best friend.

360
00:20:56,358 --> 00:21:01,062
Someday he'll shine out there and you'll
point to him and say, "That is my closest friend."

361
00:21:01,308 --> 00:21:03,602
I'm sure of it. It'll be all right.

362
00:21:05,902 --> 00:21:06,838
I know.

363
00:21:09,846 --> 00:21:13,484
As a small experiment, can you try taking over his body?

364
00:21:13,659 --> 00:21:15,064
Uh‐huh. What for?

365
00:21:15,246 --> 00:21:17,095
Like I said, it's an experiment.

366
00:21:17,199 --> 00:21:19,492
You don't say that to your test subject.

367
00:21:19,588 --> 00:21:22,097
He's the test subject, so don't worry.

368
00:21:23,368 --> 00:21:24,312
Whatever.

369
00:21:32,819 --> 00:21:33,811
Whoa! What the...?

370
00:21:34,065 --> 00:21:35,744
Thank you for indulging me.

371
00:21:35,890 --> 00:21:39,415
No, it wasn't anything much. Did you figure something out?

372
00:21:40,089 --> 00:21:41,605
I'm not sure for now.

373
00:21:42,169 --> 00:21:44,589
Just going to see how things go for a while.

374
00:21:46,431 --> 00:21:49,781
I beg you, just this once, can I
have dinner without pizza sauce?

375
00:21:51,693 --> 00:21:52,670
I'm back!

376
00:21:52,695 --> 00:21:55,043
A secret recipe of the Otosaka house.

377
00:21:55,068 --> 00:21:57,078
A cream stew full of broccoli!

378
00:21:57,103 --> 00:21:58,459
It's red!

379
00:21:58,737 --> 00:22:01,585
But cream stew is supposed to be white, isn't it?

380
00:22:01,610 --> 00:22:04,269
That is what makes it a secret family recipe.

381
00:22:04,654 --> 00:22:06,226
Just as I thought.

382
00:22:06,599 --> 00:22:08,305
What do I believe in, you ask?

383
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:10,551
I have to believe in myself, of course.

384
00:22:10,916 --> 00:22:11,764
The power to believe...

385
00:22:11,789 --> 00:22:14,765
Oh! It's a new commercial from Yusarin.

386
00:22:14,790 --> 00:22:16,870
And it's How‐Low‐Hello's new song.

387
00:22:17,306 --> 00:22:21,003
That reminds me, did Yusarin really
transfer to your school, Big Brother?

388
00:22:21,384 --> 00:22:22,235
Yeah.

389
00:22:22,441 --> 00:22:27,485
That is just... so incredibly amazing!

